article.headline: Presbyterian 59, Army 43
article.story: WEST POINT, N.Y. -- Al'Lonzo Coleman had 14 points, 10 rebounds and four steals to lead Presbyterian over Army 59-43 on Monday night. Bryan Bostic added 12 points and Josh Johnson 11 for Presbyterian (2-4). Jesse Steele and Nathan Hedgecock each scored seven points for Army (1-6), which lost its sixth straight game. The Blue Hose shot 48.9 percent, including 62.5 percent (10-of-16) in the second half. They outrebounded the Black Knights 32-20, the sixth straight time Army was beaten on the boards. Hedgecock got the Black Knights off to a fast start, hitting his first three shots, but Army went 3-for-17 from the field for the remainder of the opening period and fell behind 28-16 at the break.
